  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While the offense is a breach of fiduciary duty, the 10-year suggestion from the public is disproportionate to the amount embezzled. Balancing the severity of the theft with the defendant's lack of a criminal record, a sentence of 6 months is sufficient to serve as a deterrent without being punitive to an unnecessary extent.",
  "verdict": 6
}
